<p>I have a route like this:</p>  <pre><code>  $stateProvider.state('show', {     url:   "/page/:uuid/:title",     views: {       "":       {         templateUrl: ThemePrefix + '/views/ShowCase.html',         controller:  'ShowCtrl',         resolve:     {           ShowDate: function (SearchRequests, $stateParams) {             // This will send http request depended on uuid param             return SearchRequests.GetExtend($stateParams.uuid);           }         }       },       "footer": {         templateUrl: ThemePrefix + '/views/footer.html',         controller:  'FooterCtrl',         resolve:     {           Popularareas: function (WebServices) {             // This will send another http request             return WebServices.GetPopularAreas();           }         }       }     }   }) </code></pre>  <p>The <code>title</code> param in url, can be a Persian word, separated by <code>-</code>.</p>  <p><em>(e.g. <code>domain.com/page/53f198db0fdf0/مثال-با-فاصله</code>)</em></p>  <p>In some browsers like <code>phantomjs</code>, the router's resolve function will iterate which causes this log: <code>Watchers fired in the last 5 iterations</code> and multiple requests to server!</p>  <p>But it's work normally on chrome, firefox, and etc.</p>  <p><strong>P.S:</strong> The controller specified in route <em>(in example above <code>ShowCtrl</code>)</em>, would not execute at all in this situation.</p>